<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,903,1108]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,903,928]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</emphasis>
South and western Europe: 
<collectingCountry box="[627,693,903,927]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[706,785,904,927]" name="France" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[798,934,903,927]" name="Switzerland" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[947,999,903,927]" name="Italy" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1012,1117,903,927]" name="Germany" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1130,1229,904,928]" name="Hungary" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1241,1320,903,927]" name="Russia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Russia</collectingCountry>
. This species extends its distribution area to north-east (
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[672,839,940,964]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich 
<number box="[780,839,940,964]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[850,1016,940,964]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[956,1016,940,964]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,903,1108]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,975,1000]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Biology.</emphasis>
Species of sandy sites, in southern Europe common in such localities. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herrmann" box="[1086,1281,975,999]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Herrmann, M. (2006) Wirtsbindung und Habitate der Blutbiene Sphecodes ruficrus (Erichson 1835). Mitteilungen der entomologische Vereins in Stuttgart, 41, 55 - 60." type="journal article" year="2006">
Herrmann (
<number box="[1214,1273,975,999]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the biology and hosts. The main host is 
<taxonomicName box="[551,734,1012,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis box="[551,734,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Andrena humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also related species 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez" authorityName="Perez" box="[970,1134,1012,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="livens">
<emphasis box="[970,1065,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. livens</emphasis>
Pérez
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Giraud" authorityName="Giraud" box="[1187,1395,1012,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taraxaci">
<emphasis box="[1187,1311,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. taraxaci</emphasis>
Giraud
</taxonomicName>
are possible hosts of this species. We have studied this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[852,916,1047,1071]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Spain</collectingCountry>
in association with 
<taxonomicName box="[1142,1239,1048,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="livens">
<emphasis box="[1142,1239,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. livens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[1255,1436,1047,1071]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich (
<number box="[1369,1427,1047,1071]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck" authorityName="Schenck" box="[251,561,1084,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[251,459,1084,1108]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Andrena decipiens</emphasis>
Schenck
</taxonomicName>
as a host, but with no further details.
</paragraph>
